| **Key lesson for Image Foundry** | The two-part positioning structure (identity + differentiator) is highly transferable: “We’re a CGI and visualisation studio. From your CAD files to finished marketing imagery, everything is produced by our team.” |

## 3.4  Instrument

| **URL** | [instrument.com](https://www.instrument.com/) |
| --- | --- |
| **Type** | Digital-first brand, product and marketing agency — Portland, USA |
| **Clients** | Nike, Google, Netflix, Spotify, Pinterest, Microsoft, Patagonia, Uber, Marriott, Instagram, Sephora, NBA, Nordstrom, Stripe, Salesforce, Levi’s, PayPal, Oura |
| **Hero Headline** | “We’re a digital-first design agency working at the intersection of creativity and technology.” |
| **Page Structure** | Headline → project grid (filterable by brand/marketing/product) → ‘Select Clients’ list → purpose statement → news articles → services |
| **Primary CTA** | No single CTA. Services section ends with “See our offerings.” Client list is the main conversion mechanism. |
| **Social Proof Method** | The ‘Select Clients’ section is an extraordinarily comprehensive logo/name list. Displaying Nike, Netflix and Patagonia in the same list does enormous credibility work without a single testimonial. |
| **Visual Style** | Clean, typographically strong, light. Highly professional but not cold. Editorial articles are positioned prominently — signals that this is an agency that thinks, not just executes. |
